  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM6.6.4">
<l>paiṅkaṇā ḷariyuruvāy veruva nōkkip paruvaraittō ḷiraṇiyaṉaip paṟṟi vāṅki</l>
<l>aṅkaivā ḷukirnutiyā lavaṉa tāka maṅkuruti poṅkuvittā ṉaṭikkīḻ niṟpīr</l>
<l>veṅkaṇmā kaḷiṟunti veṇṇi yēṟṟa viṟalmaṉṉar tiṟalaḻiya vemmā vuytta</l>
<l>ceṅkaṇāṉ kōccōḻaṉ cērnta kōyil tirunaṟaiyūr maṇimāṭañ cērmiṉ kaḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>You who would stay low at the feet of him who,</l>
<l rend="indent">taking the form of a green-eyed man-lion,</l>
<l rend="indent">glaring so that [others] were terrified,</l>
<l>Seizing and dragging Hiraṇya with thick, boulder[-like] arms,</l>
<l rend="indent">with the tips of the sharp claws of his beautiful hand,</l>
<l rend="indent">made fluid blood boil from that one’s chest,</l>
<l>Gather at the beautiful raised shrine in Tirunaṟaiyūr,</l>
<l rend="indent">the temple where came Ceṅkaṇāṉ, the Cōla king</l>
<l>Who sent his fierce elephant to destroy the strength of brave kings</l>
<l rend="indent">who opposed [him] at Veṇṇi, riding fierce-eyed huge elephants.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
